Class Hall

  • java.lang.Object
    • Entities.Hall
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Hall
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Represents a Hall created for each Cineplex. Each Hall can only be assigned to one Cineplex
    Since:
    2017-11-16
    See Also:

    • Field Detail

      • classRate

        public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Double> classRate
        Class Rates will be stored in a HashMap with Hall Class Type as key and the corresponding rates as key-values. HashMap is used to create unique and non-duplicate key-value entry. 3 Different Keys: Silver/Gold/Platinum. HashMap

    • Constructor Detail

      • Hall

        public Hall(java.lang.String hallClass,
            java.lang.String hallCode,
            java.lang.String cineplex,
            int capacity,
            int rows,
            int columns)
        Create a new Hall for each cineplex when given hallClass, hallCode, cineplex, capacity, rows, columns. classRate will be initialized with NULL value.
        Parameters:
        hallClass - This Hall's hall class type.
        hallCode - This Hall's unique hall code.
        cineplex - This Hall's cineplex it is assigned to.
        hallCode - This Hall's hall code.
        capacity - This Hall's maximum capacity.
        rows - This Hall's rows of seats.
        columns - This Hall's columns of seats.

      • updateClassRate

        public void updateClassRate(java.lang.String hallClass,
                            java.lang.Double rate)
        Changes the hall class rates of different hall class types (Eg. Silver, Gold, Platinum). A HashMap is used, so that it creates a unique entry for each hall class rate
        Parameters:
        hallClass - Represents hall class to update the rate.
        rate - Represents the new rate to be updated
